Concert of the "students of the velvet revolution" with song ensembles of the Karl's university
Now the festival Festa Academica already offers for the third time the amalgamation of the world student day with the anniversary of the velvet revolution and this with music experience.
In the course of the festival fancy to twenty professional choirs and university choirs.
A main focus of the festival are both concerts which take place on the 17th of November.
"The Karl's university has big portion in the festival."
"Among the participants the choir of the educational faculty and the faculty is also represented for humanistic studies and, among the rest, in the festival committee the rector Václav Hampl also sits", the leader of the organisation team, Jakub Čaloun stated.
Absolute climax of the festival is the public concert of professional school choirs which takes place on the 17th of November from 14 o'clock on the place before the national technical library in Dejvice.
The composition of the important Czech jazz musician Karel Rů ž ička "Celebration jazz measure" stands on the programme.
In the evening hours takes place in the gala rooms of the national house in Vinohrady the concert "students of the velvet revolution" (Studenty sametu) with which also university choirs appear choirs of the Karl's university not impossible.
Festa Academica puts to itself the aim to celebrate not only the world student day solemnly and to think the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but to present choral music at the highest level to the public and to promote the creative cooperation of young people.
Main organizer is the union of Czech choirs in cooperation with the Johannes Kepler high school.
Bohuslav Svoboda, the chief burgomaster of the capital of Prague and Václav Hampl, the rector of the Karl's university took over the patronage about the whole event.
Das Fest findet vom 16. bis zum 20. November in Prag und in Pardubice statt.
The expiry plan encloses except festival concerts also numerous music meetings, Studenten-Happanings, Matinees and other events.
